The supported HPE Apollo 4200 Gen9 server must meet the
below requirements in order to use this set of OEMID
flavor files:

- Model: ProLiant XL420 Gen9
- Virtual CPUs: 40 (hyperthreading assumed)
- Total memory: 64GB minimum
- OS: Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.4
- ??RAID controller details??
- Disks: 24x physical disks minimum ??size??
- SSD: 1x NVMe ??size??
- Network:
  - Device eno1 connected to management network
  - Devices ens1f0 and ens2f0 connected
    to storage network

Additional software packages:
  - hpssacli for command-line RAID management
    (This can be automatically installed from
     the Internet by the Gluster Colonizer)

Operating system requirements:
  - Red Hat Gluster Storage ??version??
  - Ansible ??version??
  - User 'ansible' on all nodes with the same
    password and with sudo privleges
  - firewalld service enabled
  - NetworkManager service enabled
  - iptables service _not_ enabled
  - SELinux enabled and enforcing
